20
00:02:37,608 --> 00:02:45,295
[SPEAKER_07]: 26-116 offered by President Behrs and Councilor Seng, resolution to celebrate Marie Cassidy and her years of service and devotion to the children and city of Medford.

21
00:02:45,595 --> 00:02:51,381
[SPEAKER_07]: Be it resolved by the Medford City Council that we congratulate Marie Cassidy on her retirement as director of the Medford Family Network.

22
00:02:51,926 --> 00:03:02,500
[SPEAKER_07]: and thank her for decades of public service to the city of Medford, especially her 33 years as the heart and soul of the MFN, which has been essential to building thriving childhoods and community connections for generations of children and parents in our city.

23
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:03,181
[SPEAKER_07]: Councillor Singh.

24
00:03:04,403 --> 00:03:07,787
[SPEAKER_09]: Thank you, President Behrs, for letting me join you on this.

25
00:03:10,438 --> 00:03:20,402
[SPEAKER_09]: Marie is one of those members of our community who has given her whole life to our community, to folks who she doesn't know.

26
00:03:21,082 --> 00:03:25,684
[SPEAKER_09]: And she touches their life in a way that I think is immeasurable.

27
00:03:26,224 --> 00:03:35,048
[SPEAKER_09]: For the children growing up in Medford, I think a lot of us will remember the activities that they've held for the parents in Medford.

28
00:03:37,441 --> 00:03:43,286
[SPEAKER_09]: The MFN and her work in guiding and creating events for the MFN has just made their lives easier as well.

29
00:03:45,107 --> 00:03:53,695
[SPEAKER_09]: When we think about what this world is missing today and something that Medford is pretty good at, I'd say is that building of community.

30
00:03:53,995 --> 00:04:04,804
[SPEAKER_09]: And Marie is one of those reasons why we have such a strong community and such a strong fabric of parents' networks, of children's networks, and friendships here in the city.

31
00:04:05,923 --> 00:04:10,346
[SPEAKER_09]: It was extraordinary to see the love for her at the teddy bear picnic a few weeks ago.

32
00:04:11,506 --> 00:04:19,191
[SPEAKER_09]: Extraordinary to see so many people come out and just record videos and say, you know, share the love with her.

33
00:04:19,912 --> 00:04:22,653
[SPEAKER_09]: And she deserves every bit of this and even more.

34
00:04:23,034 --> 00:04:26,556
[SPEAKER_09]: So thank you, Marie, for your service to Medford.

35
00:04:29,498 --> 00:04:30,418
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you, Councilor Sang.

36
00:04:30,438 --> 00:04:31,879
[SPEAKER_07]: Councilor Scarpelli.

37
00:04:31,919 --> 00:04:32,740
[SPEAKER_21]: Thank you, Mr. President.

38
00:04:34,118 --> 00:04:36,420
[SPEAKER_21]: Great job for my colleagues to put this on the agenda.

39
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:50,290
[SPEAKER_21]: I think that knowing Marie Cassidy in many different levels, one as a colleague, as a teacher, former teacher, and then as a parent of two young members at the time for the Meffitt Family Network.

40
00:04:51,071 --> 00:04:59,657
[SPEAKER_21]: And the efforts that Marie Cassidy allowed us to become better parents and

41
00:05:01,017 --> 00:05:08,722
[SPEAKER_21]: give us the opportunity to network with other young parents and that opportunity still exists today because of her efforts.

42
00:05:08,842 --> 00:05:13,906
[SPEAKER_21]: I know that my biggest regret is missing her party the other night.

43
00:05:13,966 --> 00:05:15,507
[SPEAKER_21]: We had a zoning meeting here.

44
00:05:20,125 --> 00:05:27,509
[SPEAKER_21]: And again, it's sometimes these are the pains of this office that you miss important opportunities to thank people.

45
00:05:27,969 --> 00:05:37,674
[SPEAKER_21]: So I thank my colleagues for bringing this forward tonight so we can publicly thank Marie Cassidy for everything she's done for our community and how many people she's touched in a positive light.

46
00:05:37,694 --> 00:05:41,036
[SPEAKER_21]: So thank you, Marie, and thank you for my colleagues presenting this.

47
00:05:42,677 --> 00:05:43,797
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you, Councilor Scarpelli.

48
00:05:43,817 --> 00:05:44,538
[SPEAKER_07]: Councilor Callahan.

49
00:05:46,548 --> 00:05:53,314
[SPEAKER_14]: Thanks, I just want to comment how much people in other cities wish they had the Medford Family Network.

50
00:05:53,754 --> 00:06:04,624
[SPEAKER_14]: It is truly amazing and just such an incredible service to so many families and so many people have met great, great friends through that network when their children were young.

51
00:06:04,884 --> 00:06:08,588
[SPEAKER_14]: So it's really an incredible service that she's done for our community and thank you so much.

52
00:06:08,608 --> 00:06:10,970
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you.

53
00:06:13,197 --> 00:06:19,663
[SPEAKER_07]: I know Marie has received a lot of accolades and celebrations over the last couple of months and really over the last year.

54
00:06:20,223 --> 00:06:35,137
[SPEAKER_07]: And we do have a paper on tonight as well to talk about Medford Family Network and some funding to help them address a significant loss of grant funds due to the federal government's cutbacks on services for kids, education, healthcare, et cetera.

55
00:06:35,957 --> 00:06:37,139
[SPEAKER_07]: So we will be talking about that.

56
00:06:37,259 --> 00:06:39,581
[SPEAKER_07]: But Marie founded the MFN.

57
00:06:41,258 --> 00:06:46,961
[SPEAKER_07]: 33 years ago, and it has literally helped generations of kids in our city thrive.

58
00:06:47,922 --> 00:06:56,306
[SPEAKER_07]: And I can't think of anyone more universally celebrated as just a kind and caring person who has made the lives of families in our city better than Marie Cassidy.

59
00:06:56,946 --> 00:07:04,029
[SPEAKER_07]: And, you know, I said to her congratulations on her retirement at a retirement party, and she was like, congratulations.

60
00:07:05,130 --> 00:07:05,830
[SPEAKER_07]: It's bittersweet.

61
00:07:06,971 --> 00:07:07,491
[SPEAKER_07]: She was like,

62
00:07:08,573 --> 00:07:09,093
[SPEAKER_07]: She's bummed.

63
00:07:09,673 --> 00:07:10,694
[SPEAKER_07]: She really loves this job.

64
00:07:10,754 --> 00:07:12,034
[SPEAKER_07]: She really loves the kids in Medford.

65
00:07:12,094 --> 00:07:15,115
[SPEAKER_07]: And what she also said to me is that she's going to be around.

66
00:07:15,475 --> 00:07:24,058
[SPEAKER_07]: So she may be retiring from the full-time job, but she will continue to be supporting the MFN and our city and our kids.

67
00:07:25,979 --> 00:07:28,120
[SPEAKER_07]: On the motion of councilor saying to approve, seconded by?

68
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:30,660
[SPEAKER_07]: Seconded by Councilor Mullane.

