447
00:45:11,747 --> 00:45:20,094
[SPEAKER_07]: You said the bond ratings agencies look at us to have both in capital stabilization and quote unquote free cash, a certain amount of money.

448
00:45:20,634 --> 00:45:23,036
[SPEAKER_07]: We established stabilization funds two years ago.

449
00:45:23,196 --> 00:45:24,117
[SPEAKER_07]: That's a new thing for us.

450
00:45:24,197 --> 00:45:25,518
[SPEAKER_07]: Before that, it was always free cash.

451
00:45:25,558 --> 00:45:26,299
[SPEAKER_07]: Now we have these things.

452
00:45:28,333 --> 00:45:38,322
[SPEAKER_07]: DLS also look and DOR also look at that recommendation when they say you should have about 10 or 15 percent of your annual budget in reserves.

453
00:45:38,482 --> 00:45:41,965
[SPEAKER_07]: Are they just talking about free cash or are they talking about all of our reserves?

454
00:45:45,648 --> 00:45:45,989
[SPEAKER_07]: All of it.

