489
00:49:07,816 --> 00:49:09,777
[SPEAKER_11]: local workforce to do this project.

490
00:49:10,417 --> 00:49:20,859
[SPEAKER_11]: We represent 75,000 men and women around the state, and we train 74% of all construction apprentices in the Commonwealth of Massachusetts.

491
00:49:21,219 --> 00:49:26,881
[SPEAKER_11]: We're the ones doing the hard work to make sure that the construction industry has that skilled workforce.

492
00:49:27,561 --> 00:49:33,903
[SPEAKER_11]: And this study or determination is in compliance with Chapter 238 of the Acts of 2024,

493
00:49:36,484 --> 00:49:38,925
[SPEAKER_11]: which allowed the use of project labor agreements.

494
00:49:38,965 --> 00:49:47,990
[SPEAKER_11]: This is one of the steps that is required under that statute, and I can guarantee you that you will be happy with the results.

495
00:49:48,970 --> 00:49:57,655
[SPEAKER_11]: In addition to the quality project that I discussed, there's great opportunities for the workers in Medford and the surrounding communities.

496
00:50:00,716 --> 00:50:02,097
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you, Mr. President.

497
00:50:03,218 --> 00:50:03,518
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you.

498
00:50:04,743 --> 00:50:08,847
[SPEAKER_07]: All right, anyone else who'd like to speak on this paper?

