530
00:52:40,357 --> 00:52:50,983
[SPEAKER_07]: Dear President Behrs and city councilors, as you are aware, the city is working in coordination with MassDOT to construct traffic and safety improvements to the Main Street Corridor, beginning just south of Thomas Street and extending just north of

531
00:52:51,845 --> 00:52:58,688
[SPEAKER_07]: The westbound mystic valley parkway on and off ramps the work area also extends on mystic have 38 from Main Street to just be on Union Street.

532
00:52:59,188 --> 00:53:09,712
[SPEAKER_07]: Project blood traffic signals to the 3 major intersections and include roadway mill and overlay intersection geometry revisions and improvements to sidewalks bus lanes bicycle lanes crosswalk signage and pavement markings.

533
00:53:10,320 --> 00:53:15,523
[SPEAKER_07]: The federal funding granted for this project requires that the right-of-way be in complete ownership and physical control of the city.

534
00:53:16,043 --> 00:53:20,285
[SPEAKER_07]: A survey prepared for the project identified nine private properties that contain public infrastructure.

535
00:53:20,726 --> 00:53:29,210
[SPEAKER_07]: The city needs to acquire permanent and temporary easements as part of the project to facilitate the reconstruction of sidewalks, drive Wances' entrances, and relocating overhead wires.

536
00:53:29,230 --> 00:53:35,994
[SPEAKER_07]: The project also requires the city to alter the layouts of Main Street and Mystic Avenue to include within the said layouts the public infrastructure on private properties.

537
00:53:36,534 --> 00:53:39,676
[SPEAKER_07]: Layout alterations have been approved by the Mayor and by the Community Development Board.

538
00:53:40,283 --> 00:53:42,364
[SPEAKER_07]: Enclosed are the following documents for your consideration.

539
00:53:42,384 --> 00:53:55,009
[SPEAKER_07]: A city council order to acquire the easements, the order of taking to take the easements by eminent domain, an order of alteration of layout to alter the layout of Main Street and Mystic Avenue, the alteration plan and the recommendation of the Community Development Board.

540
00:53:55,449 --> 00:54:03,212
[SPEAKER_07]: The easements were appraised by a certified general appraiser and those appraisals were reviewed by a certified general review appraiser to establish just compensation for the easements.

541
00:54:03,732 --> 00:54:06,793
[SPEAKER_07]: Written offers were sent to all nine property owners via certified mail on May 6, 2026.

542
00:54:08,481 --> 00:54:11,869
[SPEAKER_07]: Assistant City Engineer Sierra Schatz has been in contact with each owner to answer.

543
00:54:12,973 --> 00:54:17,095
[SPEAKER_07]: questions and address concerns throughout this process, beginning with an initial contact letter sent in February 2026.

544
00:54:17,215 --> 00:54:28,199
[SPEAKER_07]: I respectfully request the City Council adopt the order approving the acquisition of the easements to execute the order of taking effectuating the acquisition and the order of alteration of layouts at your regular June 23rd, 2026 meeting.

545
00:54:28,700 --> 00:54:32,501
[SPEAKER_07]: Assistant City Engineer Sierra Schatz will be in attendance to answer questions on this matter.

