01:14:01,253 --> 01:14:11,202
[SPEAKER_07]: I think at this point we, I don't, I know there's some residents who are here who, I think some of them are folks who are specifically property owners who are affected by the proposal.

763
01:14:12,263 --> 01:14:19,229
[SPEAKER_07]: If there's anything else you want to add at this point, please do and then I'll recognize the members of the public if they want to speak on this.

764
01:14:20,657 --> 01:14:29,759
[SPEAKER_15]: Okay, all right, yeah, thank you all for your feedback, and once again, I really appreciate the opportunity to try this again.

765
01:14:29,779 --> 01:14:37,280
[SPEAKER_15]: I thank you for your cooperation, as I've never done this before, and I'll come better prepared next time, so thank you for your feedback.

766
01:14:38,980 --> 01:14:39,940
[SPEAKER_07]: Yeah, it's not.

767
01:14:41,621 --> 01:14:44,641
[SPEAKER_07]: As a fellow, it seems to me, perfectionist, I understand.

768
01:14:44,661 --> 01:14:47,422
[SPEAKER_07]: I understand that we want to get it right on round one.

769
01:14:50,954 --> 01:14:52,055
[SPEAKER_07]: I've only done one of these.

770
01:14:52,315 --> 01:14:54,196
[SPEAKER_07]: I've been on the council almost seven years.

