01:15:50,505 --> 01:15:52,546
[SPEAKER_07]: So welcome, and if you could just give us your name and.

780
01:15:52,606 --> 01:15:53,566
[SPEAKER_12]: Yes, good evening.

781
01:15:53,926 --> 01:15:55,366
[SPEAKER_12]: My name is Thuy Trung.

782
01:15:55,386 --> 01:15:58,367
[SPEAKER_12]: I am one of the owner of the impact properties.

783
01:15:58,927 --> 01:16:01,268
[SPEAKER_12]: And so the other owners over here as well.

784
01:16:02,088 --> 01:16:04,708
[SPEAKER_12]: First and foremost, I support this project.

785
01:16:05,429 --> 01:16:14,851
[SPEAKER_12]: However, I do have some concerns in terms of the communication process, which you already addressed, so thank you, and the evaluation process.

786
01:16:16,331 --> 01:16:18,552
[SPEAKER_12]: Since we haven't received any

787
01:16:19,492 --> 01:16:24,493
[SPEAKER_12]: letters for some reason, but Sierra did send it to me today, so thank you for the prompt response.

788
01:16:25,353 --> 01:16:28,974
[SPEAKER_12]: That says, I just literally received the letter today.

789
01:16:29,715 --> 01:16:33,676
[SPEAKER_12]: Respectfully, I do have three, I would like to raise three requests.

790
01:16:34,496 --> 01:16:43,218
[SPEAKER_12]: Number one, I would like to have the supporting document and the, that explain the determination of the evaluation.

791
01:16:43,978 --> 01:16:46,459
[SPEAKER_12]: Number two, we would like to have more times.

792
01:16:47,980 --> 01:16:55,844
[SPEAKER_12]: And number three, since we just received it today, I would like to have more times and a chance to do our own evaluations.

793
01:16:56,564 --> 01:16:59,906
[SPEAKER_12]: I'm simply not objecting this project.

794
01:17:00,526 --> 01:17:09,571
[SPEAKER_12]: We just want to ensure that we are fully informed and our properties is being fairly and properly evaluated and compensated.

795
01:17:10,091 --> 01:17:10,431
[SPEAKER_12]: Thank you.

796
01:17:10,451 --> 01:17:11,131
[SPEAKER_12]: Great.

797
01:17:11,412 --> 01:17:12,032
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you so much.

798
01:17:13,788 --> 01:17:20,873
[SPEAKER_07]: Is there anyone else who'd like to speak about this order, proposed order of taking at this time, either in person or on Zoom?

799
01:17:22,915 --> 01:17:23,215
[SPEAKER_07]: All right.

800
01:17:23,935 --> 01:17:26,337
[SPEAKER_07]: Owen, I think that might be the city engineer, Owen.

801
01:17:27,318 --> 01:17:29,119
[SPEAKER_07]: So I will recognize you, Owen.

802
01:17:31,341 --> 01:17:31,601
[SPEAKER_16]: Hi.

803
01:17:31,641 --> 01:17:31,881
[SPEAKER_16]: Thank you.

804
01:17:31,921 --> 01:17:32,482
[SPEAKER_16]: Can you hear me?

805
01:17:33,462 --> 01:17:34,103
[SPEAKER_08]: Yes, we can hear you.

806
01:17:34,643 --> 01:17:34,964
[SPEAKER_16]: Great.

807
01:17:35,444 --> 01:17:39,527
[SPEAKER_16]: So just to answer some of the questions that you guys had here.

808
01:17:40,498 --> 01:17:42,178
[SPEAKER_16]: You know, this is a state project.

809
01:17:42,258 --> 01:17:47,299
[SPEAKER_16]: This is something that we've been working with the state since February to do.

810
01:17:47,359 --> 01:17:59,722
[SPEAKER_16]: We have been in contact with all the property owners, and we have had an appraisal by a third party to appraise all of their properties within the last few months.

811
01:18:00,342 --> 01:18:03,182
[SPEAKER_16]: So these are up-to-date numbers.

812
01:18:03,243 --> 01:18:05,683
[SPEAKER_16]: These are up-to-date figures of what their properties are worth.

813
01:18:06,355 --> 01:18:18,718
[SPEAKER_16]: And these easements and temporary easements and permanent easements are only slivers, like little slivers of land that are currently sidewalk and will continue to be sidewalk.

814
01:18:19,698 --> 01:18:20,198
[SPEAKER_16]: That's all.

815
01:18:20,859 --> 01:18:24,639
[SPEAKER_16]: So this is just a formal process of how to take the land.

816
01:18:25,980 --> 01:18:26,900
[SPEAKER_16]: Going back to Ms.

817
01:18:27,640 --> 01:18:35,062
[SPEAKER_16]: Kelland's question about what is actually going on, there's technically three blinking red lights

818
01:18:35,980 --> 01:18:52,993
[SPEAKER_16]: at the Route 16 underpass and at the Main Street-Mystic Ave intersection, all of those will be turned to working lights, and that is what this project is about.

819
01:18:53,073 --> 01:18:53,854
[SPEAKER_16]: It's about safety.

820
01:18:54,675 --> 01:18:57,337
[SPEAKER_16]: If anybody has been through there lately, you know that it is

821
01:18:58,118 --> 01:19:01,579
[SPEAKER_16]: completely a mess during rush hour.

822
01:19:01,859 --> 01:19:03,800
[SPEAKER_16]: So this is all about a safety improvement.

823
01:19:03,900 --> 01:19:12,682
[SPEAKER_16]: It's about a little bit of widening of roads so that there's just a little more breathing room for two lanes of traffic, for bikes, for pedestrians.

824
01:19:13,823 --> 01:19:16,384
[SPEAKER_16]: And that's what this whole project is about.

825
01:19:16,864 --> 01:19:20,645
[SPEAKER_16]: But if you have any other questions, I am here to answer those.

826
01:19:21,345 --> 01:19:21,585
[SPEAKER_21]: Thanks.

827
01:19:23,706 --> 01:19:24,146
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you.

828
01:19:24,466 --> 01:19:26,487
[SPEAKER_07]: I do have Councillor Scarpelli.

829
01:19:27,599 --> 01:19:43,111
