919
01:26:28,895 --> 01:26:29,135
[SPEAKER_07]: Yes.

920
01:26:29,155 --> 01:26:31,536
[SPEAKER_07]: I move the affirmative, the negative, the motion passes.

921
01:26:31,636 --> 01:26:33,237
[SPEAKER_07]: We'll take this back up on July 14th.

922
01:26:38,843 --> 01:26:47,073
[SPEAKER_07]: Two paper motions, orders, and resolutions, paper 26118 offered by Councilor Scarpelli, resolution to appeal deficient public records response of city administration regarding legal matters.

923
01:26:47,854 --> 01:26:54,342
[SPEAKER_07]: Whereas on April 29th, 2026, the city council through its president, Isaac Beres, filed a public records request to the law department, Janice Spencer.

924
01:26:54,862 --> 01:26:57,744
[SPEAKER_07]: Seeking various public records, this request is set forth in council paper 26077.

925
01:26:59,305 --> 01:27:11,334
[SPEAKER_07]: And whereas this council's April 29th request was substantially based on the failure of the administration to respond to our request for records and information sent to it by the council in February 2026 in council paper 26043.

926
01:27:11,934 --> 01:27:19,560
[SPEAKER_07]: And whereas on May 13th, 2026, Janice Spencer filed a request with the public records division seeking an additional 30 days to respond to the council's request.

927
01:27:20,000 --> 01:27:24,382
[SPEAKER_07]: The request for an extension of 30 days to respond was granted by the supervisor of records on May 19th, 2026.

928
01:27:25,243 --> 01:27:41,672
[SPEAKER_07]: And whereas on Tuesday, June 16th, 2026, Nina Nasarian on behalf of the administration sent a series of five emails to the city council in which she attached a small handful of settlement agreements including one that included a confidentiality provision in spite of the fact that the mayor had previously stated to the council that the city does not have non-disclosure agreements.

929
01:27:41,912 --> 01:27:47,355
[SPEAKER_07]: And whereas the extended period for the city to respond had expired, now therefore be it resolved by the Medford City Council

930
01:27:47,815 --> 01:27:58,925
[SPEAKER_07]: Then in light of the sparse and inadequate response of the administration, along with the questionable veracity of its prior statements, we authorize by roll call vote an appeal of the administration's response to the Secretary of State's Office Public Records Division.

931
01:27:59,485 --> 01:28:00,406
[SPEAKER_07]: Counselor Scarpelli.

932
01:28:01,447 --> 01:28:02,348
[SPEAKER_21]: Thank you, Mr. President.

933
01:28:03,489 --> 01:28:07,092
[SPEAKER_21]: I think this resolution speaks for itself.

934
01:28:07,312 --> 01:28:14,899
[SPEAKER_21]: I think that we have asked this administration to present to us a pretty detailed breakdown

935
01:28:15,658 --> 01:28:32,144
[SPEAKER_21]: when it comes to our fiscal responsibilities for council, especially for what is being released publicly with lawsuits from our city administration to our city employees and on.

936
01:28:34,565 --> 01:28:39,747
[SPEAKER_21]: What we heard from the administration is that this is a lot of work, that what we're asking for

937
01:28:41,058 --> 01:29:04,070
[SPEAKER_21]: is really too much to compose and present that we then received a breakdown from the mayor asking us that from our request that if we took some items off the table, then she would then grant us some of our requests that we've asked for in this budget cycle.

938
01:29:06,171 --> 01:29:08,692
[SPEAKER_21]: To me, I think this is so disingenuine

939
01:29:09,447 --> 01:29:20,598
[SPEAKER_21]: and the fact that we received multiple emails from the administration that makes no sense to this counselor.

940
01:29:21,158 --> 01:29:27,665
[SPEAKER_21]: It is a breakdown of a process that shows

941
01:29:28,782 --> 01:29:34,765
[SPEAKER_21]: who is using what law line or not even a figure.

942
01:29:35,526 --> 01:29:37,387
[SPEAKER_21]: This is something very simple we asked for.

943
01:29:38,187 --> 01:29:51,775
[SPEAKER_21]: The Freedom of Information Act that we requested was broken down step by step so we can see the true impact of the legal issues and concerns that have been brought up time after time to this council.

944
01:29:53,062 --> 01:29:59,509
[SPEAKER_21]: And what we've been getting back is trivial rhetoric that makes no sense.

945
01:29:59,789 --> 01:30:02,873
[SPEAKER_21]: I personally, as one counselor, do not care.

946
01:30:03,877 --> 01:30:07,500
[SPEAKER_21]: what neighboring communities spend on a line.

947
01:30:08,081 --> 01:30:23,095
[SPEAKER_21]: To say that we, in communication, that we can't actually get the information financially of what we're paying out because there are different outsourced, different departments, to me is very confusing.

948
01:30:25,954 --> 01:30:29,855
[SPEAKER_21]: This is an administration that has all this at the tip of their finger.

949
01:30:30,195 --> 01:30:35,396
[SPEAKER_21]: And it really frightens me for the fact that this is taking us this long.

950
01:30:36,777 --> 01:30:54,101
[SPEAKER_21]: This is just a true indication of what we need to know before we can vote on a budget, truly vote on a budget, that has our financial responsibility attached to it.

951
01:30:55,536 --> 01:30:59,877
[SPEAKER_21]: We are the fiscal stewards of this community.

952
01:31:00,737 --> 01:31:01,737
[SPEAKER_21]: And that's our job.

953
01:31:01,917 --> 01:31:14,640
[SPEAKER_21]: And we've been saying since February, please give us this information so we know that there isn't a gap or there isn't an ulterior issue here in where we're spending our money.

954
01:31:18,601 --> 01:31:23,542
[SPEAKER_21]: And to get back some of the information from our administration just makes no sense.

955
01:31:25,340 --> 01:31:33,043
[SPEAKER_21]: to say that we don't have a way, a mechanism in place to understand where that financial breakdown comes from is befuddling to me.

956
01:31:33,924 --> 01:31:46,309
[SPEAKER_21]: When we used to get month to month, remember those days we used to get the breakdown and you used to scan down, you go to school department and you saw KP law, KP law, KP law, KP law.

957
01:31:46,589 --> 01:31:50,331
[SPEAKER_21]: Then you went to the fire line, it said KP law, KP law, KP law.

958
01:31:50,711 --> 01:31:52,912
[SPEAKER_21]: It's there, it just has to be presented.

959
01:31:54,275 --> 01:31:58,557
[SPEAKER_21]: But for some reason, we can't manufacture that in this community.

960
01:32:00,398 --> 01:32:01,299
[SPEAKER_21]: To me, that's frightening.

961
01:32:02,139 --> 01:32:03,640
[SPEAKER_21]: To me, that sends a bad message.

962
01:32:04,540 --> 01:32:08,182
[SPEAKER_21]: So, Mr. President, with this resolution, it's very simplistic.

963
01:32:09,623 --> 01:32:19,168
[SPEAKER_21]: It's sending this off to the next layer in the state to figure out what our next options are, because our

964
01:32:20,514 --> 01:32:26,438
[SPEAKER_21]: administration is not giving us the requests that we required by law.

965
01:32:27,259 --> 01:32:32,643
[SPEAKER_21]: And after given the 30 day extension, we still have yet to get the breakdown.

966
01:32:32,723 --> 01:32:36,025
[SPEAKER_21]: And by the way, just to add, this isn't just KP law, everyone.

967
01:32:37,026 --> 01:32:40,808
[SPEAKER_21]: There are multiple law firms that are being used by the city now.

968
01:32:41,909 --> 01:32:47,093
[SPEAKER_21]: So even in reference to the responses we're getting back, it says KP law.

969
01:32:47,113 --> 01:32:48,634
[SPEAKER_21]: That's just not not true.

970
01:32:48,954 --> 01:32:49,875
[SPEAKER_21]: We want to know the full

971
01:32:50,713 --> 01:33:08,400
[SPEAKER_21]: implications of the lawsuits and the arbitrations and the settlements and the pay structures for the attorney fees and any outside source or payments that have to go to private investigators that were used and such.

972
01:33:09,080 --> 01:33:09,501
[SPEAKER_21]: This isn't

973
01:33:12,187 --> 01:33:13,528
[SPEAKER_21]: This wasn't that difficult.

974
01:33:13,808 --> 01:33:17,492
[SPEAKER_21]: It was spelt out for them pretty easily to break it down.

975
01:33:17,632 --> 01:33:33,646
[SPEAKER_21]: So for this, Mr. President, I would request my colleagues to support this as we move this along to the next level so we can get the state involved in supporting us to get this information before we vote on any sort of a budget.

976
01:33:34,207 --> 01:33:38,531
[SPEAKER_21]: Because we have, I'm more nervous now today

977
01:33:40,320 --> 01:33:42,024
[SPEAKER_21]: for the information that I've been receiving.

978
01:33:42,084 --> 01:33:44,208
[SPEAKER_21]: And I could read it, Mr. President.

979
01:33:46,313 --> 01:33:46,693
[SPEAKER_21]: It doesn't...

980
01:33:47,687 --> 01:33:48,688
[SPEAKER_21]: I didn't see anything.

981
01:33:48,948 --> 01:34:08,004
[SPEAKER_21]: Again, I would have asked my city solicitor if it's possible for me to read the communications to the public, but I don't know if this is confidential or how it was presented, but we see a breakdown from many different departments and how each department uses their legal fees.

982
01:34:08,024 --> 01:34:09,085
[SPEAKER_21]: It's not a shocker.

983
01:34:09,465 --> 01:34:15,070
[SPEAKER_21]: We understand, as a council, that each department in the city is going to use

984
01:34:17,103 --> 01:34:19,964
[SPEAKER_21]: some sort of funding through legal avenues.

985
01:34:20,004 --> 01:34:20,484
[SPEAKER_21]: We know that.

986
01:34:22,145 --> 01:34:23,065
[SPEAKER_21]: That's not what we're asking.

987
01:34:24,786 --> 01:34:30,948
[SPEAKER_21]: So I would hope my colleagues support me as we move this forward.

988
01:34:31,728 --> 01:34:32,608
[SPEAKER_21]: Thank you, Mr. President.

989
01:34:34,229 --> 01:34:34,789
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you.

990
01:34:34,969 --> 01:34:39,531
[SPEAKER_07]: Any comments from members of the council on paper 26118?

