997
01:35:28,915 --> 01:35:37,281
[SPEAKER_14]: These are the kinds of questions that we want to understand because we have learned that not all settlements are coming out of the

998
01:35:39,862 --> 01:35:48,626
[SPEAKER_14]: It's very difficult for us as city councilors to understand what our total legal expenditures is.

999
01:35:49,407 --> 01:35:55,950
[SPEAKER_14]: So receiving information on one particular settlement and then on another particular settlement doesn't answer any of those questions.

1000
01:35:57,370 --> 01:36:02,732
[SPEAKER_14]: So that's the part of it that I feel like has been really too difficult.

1001
01:36:03,032 --> 01:36:04,672
[SPEAKER_14]: It should not be so difficult.

1002
01:36:05,252 --> 01:36:19,256
[SPEAKER_14]: That is information that the administration has, and that I think is the information that we would like to know, or at least I'll just speak for myself, but that I would like to know before voting on a budget.

1003
01:36:19,856 --> 01:36:21,657
[SPEAKER_14]: So I think this is where

1004
01:36:23,288 --> 01:36:28,350
[SPEAKER_14]: To me, this is where this is coming from, is this lack of the broader picture information.

1005
01:36:31,772 --> 01:36:35,373
[SPEAKER_14]: So yeah, I am also frustrated.

1006
01:36:35,653 --> 01:36:36,213
[SPEAKER_14]: I'll put it that way.

1007
01:36:36,233 --> 01:36:41,095
[SPEAKER_14]: That has been many months of us asking for information that really should be available to us.

1008
01:36:41,816 --> 01:36:42,056
[SPEAKER_14]: Thanks.

1009
