[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you, Councilor Callahan.

1010
01:36:44,277 --> 01:36:47,278
[SPEAKER_07]: Any further questions or comments, members of the council?

1011
01:36:47,398 --> 01:36:48,058
[SPEAKER_07]: Councilor Seng.

1012
01:36:48,078 --> 01:36:51,820
[SPEAKER_09]: I'll chime in just shortly to add that

1013
01:36:53,033 --> 01:36:56,814
[SPEAKER_09]: For me, personally, it's not only just about the big picture.

1014
01:36:56,914 --> 01:37:05,058
[SPEAKER_09]: When we got the list, for example, the fire services, the professional services line item, and the fire budget, and what that's been used about.

1015
01:37:05,638 --> 01:37:08,899
[SPEAKER_09]: We've got names or vague ideas of what

1016
01:37:12,025 --> 01:37:18,327
[SPEAKER_09]: what it was used about, but I think we want to understand, is this actually a good use of our money?

1017
01:37:19,648 --> 01:37:21,948
[SPEAKER_09]: What are we actually spending it on?

1018
01:37:22,028 --> 01:37:25,690
[SPEAKER_09]: What is the quote-unquote discipline that we're spending it on?

1019
01:37:26,590 --> 01:37:30,751
[SPEAKER_09]: Whether that's fair to the workers, there's no way to ascertain that from what we've gotten.

1020
01:37:34,873 --> 01:37:35,973
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you, Councilor Sang.

1021
01:37:39,617 --> 01:37:49,244
[SPEAKER_07]: And, you know, I will, obviously the administration will have the time to characterize the responses and messages that we've received.

1022
01:37:49,344 --> 01:37:57,130
[SPEAKER_07]: But, you know, we've been asking, to me, what feels like the same questions and getting a little bit more specific on them for almost six months.

1023
01:37:57,891 --> 01:37:59,592
[SPEAKER_07]: The answers are not forthcoming.

1024
01:38:01,113 --> 01:38:04,196
[SPEAKER_07]: And, you know, we got an email today that says that like last year,

1025
01:38:05,292 --> 01:38:12,639
[SPEAKER_07]: We spent $150,000 on KP Law outside counsel out of the fire department budget and like we got that information today.

1026
01:38:13,320 --> 01:38:22,789
[SPEAKER_07]: And so I just have very, very, I have a huge struggle understanding, you know, and even that was presented kind of on its own.

1027
01:38:22,829 --> 01:38:26,212
[SPEAKER_07]: We asked that very specific question a month ago during the fire department hearing.

1028
01:38:29,010 --> 01:38:37,036
[SPEAKER_07]: I have a very hard time voting for a law budget when I don't know where it is and how much it is for and what it's going towards.

1029
01:38:37,257 --> 01:38:39,018
[SPEAKER_07]: I just have a very, very hard time with that.

1030
01:38:40,619 --> 01:38:51,468
[SPEAKER_07]: I don't appreciate, frankly, the responses that, I mean, I appreciate that we've received some responses, but they are not answering the questions that we've asked.

1031
01:38:51,748 --> 01:38:53,109
[SPEAKER_07]: So that is,

1032
01:38:54,337 --> 01:38:57,085
[SPEAKER_07]: I don't know what else we can do to further clarify.

1033
01:38:57,105 --> 01:38:59,472
[SPEAKER_07]: I feel like we've sent a number of official resolutions.

1034
01:39:00,057 --> 01:39:03,058
[SPEAKER_07]: And we've also then clarified those across budget meetings.

1035
01:39:03,698 --> 01:39:06,979
[SPEAKER_07]: And I feel like we're further clarifying tonight exactly what we're looking for.

1036
01:39:06,999 --> 01:39:22,625
[SPEAKER_07]: You know, I sent an email last week that said, can you send us all the money we spent on outside council in fiscal 26 and what budgets it came from and all of the budgets in fiscal 27 where we expect to spend money on outside council.

1037
01:39:22,785 --> 01:39:28,267
[SPEAKER_07]: And I feel like if we at least had those answers, that's maybe enough information to talk about.

1038
