[SPEAKER_07]: what the law budget for the city looks like in fiscal 27.

1039
01:39:33,054 --> 01:39:41,938
[SPEAKER_07]: But, you know, we're getting pieces of that or incomplete pieces of that or a list of all the things that we might need to, that lawyers might need to do for the city.

1040
01:39:42,058 --> 01:39:49,660
[SPEAKER_07]: And I don't think the question is that we don't think that lawyers need to do stuff for the city or that the city has legal issues or that the city may need legal counsel.

1041
01:39:50,441 --> 01:39:50,881
[SPEAKER_07]: It's that

1042
01:39:52,265 --> 01:39:55,226
[SPEAKER_07]: We don't know how much money was spent on legal services in fiscal 26.

1043
01:39:55,646 --> 01:40:00,807
[SPEAKER_07]: And we don't know where in the fiscal 27 budget, there are plans to spend money on legal services.

1044
01:40:01,828 --> 01:40:07,829
[SPEAKER_07]: Nevermind then going to the second level questions that Councilor Singh was bringing up, which is like, are we doing the right thing with those funds?

1045
01:40:09,750 --> 01:40:11,170
[SPEAKER_07]: So I support this resolution.

1046
01:40:12,111 --> 01:40:12,431
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you.

1047
01:40:14,671 --> 01:40:16,552
[SPEAKER_07]: Seeing no further discussion by members of the council go to

1048
01:40:18,040 --> 01:40:21,322
[SPEAKER_07]: The public, you can raise your hand on Zoom or line up at the podium.

1049
01:40:21,342 --> 01:40:22,143
[SPEAKER_07]: We'll start at the podium.

1050
01:40:22,183 --> 01:40:26,685
[SPEAKER_07]: If you could give your name and your city and you'll have three minutes.

1051
01:40:27,166 --> 01:40:27,506
[SPEAKER_05]: All righty.

1052
01:40:28,046 --> 01:40:30,267
[SPEAKER_05]: Simon Alcindor, 44 Tainter Street.

