1579
02:28:11,510 --> 02:28:19,694
[SPEAKER_07]: I certainly will never send an email from my account or another account asking for you to pay some random bank account money to

1580
02:28:22,393 --> 02:28:26,515
[SPEAKER_07]: just come to our meeting as you have a complete and total right to when you're putting something on our agenda.

1581
02:28:28,176 --> 02:28:29,897
[SPEAKER_07]: So that phishing scam went out.

1582
02:28:30,078 --> 02:28:37,422
[SPEAKER_07]: I know that some folks saw that and were very worried or frustrated by it, and I just want to

1583
02:28:38,315 --> 02:29:05,762
[SPEAKER_07]: say that we are working with city clerk, IT, and our CPA manager to see if there are ways that we can change some of the ways that items are appearing in our agenda, specifically as results to CPC, because it looks like an AI scraped the agenda, scraped contact information from the agenda, matched that to people's contact information, and then sent an email that seemed relatively legitimate.

1584
02:29:05,822 --> 02:29:07,843
[SPEAKER_07]: Certainly, it contained a lot of the content.

1585
02:29:08,651 --> 02:29:12,612
[SPEAKER_07]: that was on our agenda, and these are getting more sophisticated.

1586
02:29:12,652 --> 02:29:28,257
[SPEAKER_07]: So I just wanted to note that before we continue, you know, that bad actors are everywhere and trying to take advantage of our city and some folks who are residents here.

1587
02:29:28,317 --> 02:29:34,299
[SPEAKER_07]: So with that, I will read the letter, and then I will recognize Theresa DuPont, unless, Theresa, you want to speak specifically to this.

1588
02:29:38,040 --> 02:29:45,296
[SPEAKER_02]: No, I'll just briefly say thank you very much for calling attention to that and we'll do what we can to continue the awareness on this.

1589
02:29:46,795 --> 02:29:47,535
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you, Teresa.

1590
02:29:47,716 --> 02:29:48,916
[SPEAKER_07]: All right.

1591
02:29:48,976 --> 02:29:49,697
[SPEAKER_07]: So here's the letter.

1592
02:29:50,677 --> 02:30:15,752
[SPEAKER_07]: Dear President Behrs and city councilors, on behalf of the Community Preservation Committee, I respect the request and recommend that your honorable body approve the following fiscal 26 recommendations of the Community Preservation Committee, requesting the appropriation of 38,000 from the CPA General Reserve to the Royal House Association to fund emergency perimeter wall repairs at Royal House and Slave Quarters Museum, and requesting the appropriation of 70,000 from CPA General Reserve to Shiloh Baptist Church of Medford to provide final contingency funding for their ADA improvements project.

1593
02:30:16,192 --> 02:30:21,173
[SPEAKER_07]: The letter, project will be tracked in the Community Preservation Fund and CBC recommendation letters will be attached and incorporated.

1594
02:30:21,193 --> 02:30:24,814
[SPEAKER_07]: Community Preservation Act Manager, Teresa DuPont, will be in attendance to address the council.

1595
02:30:24,854 --> 02:30:25,895
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you for your consideration.

1596
02:30:25,935 --> 02:30:28,636
[SPEAKER_07]: Respectfully submitted, Brianne Alago-Kern, Mayor.

1597
02:30:28,856 --> 02:30:37,578
[SPEAKER_07]: And we do have some descriptions that were attached to the agenda, including the aforementioned contact information that an AI scraped to try to scam somebody.

1598
02:30:38,718 --> 02:30:42,199
[SPEAKER_07]: So, but the information is really great and the projects are interesting.

1599
02:30:42,239 --> 02:30:44,240
[SPEAKER_07]: So I'll recognize CPA Manager, Teresa DuPont.

1600
02:30:45,757 --> 02:30:47,717
[SPEAKER_02]: Great, thank you very much, President bears.

1601
02:30:47,758 --> 02:30:48,238
[SPEAKER_02]: Good evening.

1602
02:30:48,498 --> 02:30:50,858
[SPEAKER_02]: And thank you to our esteemed members of the council.

1603
02:30:50,878 --> 02:30:55,519
[SPEAKER_02]: I'm here tonight to support these 2 recommendations of the Medford Community Preservation Commission.

1604
02:30:55,559 --> 02:30:56,300
[SPEAKER_02]: I'll try to be brief.

1605
02:30:56,340 --> 02:30:59,020
[SPEAKER_02]: I know you still have some more time on this agenda.

1606
02:30:59,981 --> 02:31:01,561
[SPEAKER_02]: I'll 1st, start with Shiloh Baptist Church.

1607
02:31:01,621 --> 02:31:02,141
[SPEAKER_02]: It's a project.

1608
02:31:02,161 --> 02:31:03,502
[SPEAKER_02]: Y'all have seen before.

1609
02:31:04,022 --> 02:31:05,262
[SPEAKER_02]: They're seeking some final.

1610
02:31:05,813 --> 02:31:10,034
[SPEAKER_02]: contingency funds in the amount of $70,000 to wrap up their ADA improvement projects.

1611
02:31:11,054 --> 02:31:20,596
[SPEAKER_02]: We're excited to share that the elevator is in, remodeling is nearly complete, but they are up against some unanticipated change orders and are seeking assistance with covering those final bills.

1612
02:31:21,797 --> 02:31:25,137
[SPEAKER_02]: I want to applaud Shiloh for their efforts in actively fundraising.

1613
02:31:25,297 --> 02:31:31,139
[SPEAKER_02]: You know, it's tough in this financial environment right now, but their efforts have raised a bit over 10,000 to assist with this project.

1614
02:31:32,777 --> 02:31:40,823
[SPEAKER_02]: you know, happy to report that the improvement projects have led to the ability of a childcare provider to open as a tenant and serve the Medford family community.

1615
02:31:40,843 --> 02:31:44,006
[SPEAKER_02]: I believe they're providing spots currently for 50 children or so.

1616
02:31:45,507 --> 02:31:51,131
[SPEAKER_02]: So this funding would see the, again, the final bills paid for their ADA improvement project.

1617
02:31:52,432 --> 02:31:57,476
[SPEAKER_02]: I'll pause to see if there's any questions on Shiloh before I go into Royal House.

1618
02:32:00,078 --> 02:32:00,578
[SPEAKER_07]: Any questions?

1619
02:32:00,618 --> 02:32:01,459
[SPEAKER_07]: Councilor Scarpelli.

1620
02:32:01,643 --> 02:32:02,224
[SPEAKER_21]: I just have one.

1621
02:32:02,244 --> 02:32:19,326
[SPEAKER_21]: Mr. Dupont, I apologize, but again, just to be clear, no matter what we say every meeting, that the process that the CPA goes through for private churches falls into

1622
02:32:20,227 --> 02:32:26,533
[SPEAKER_21]: our category and it is legal and it fills all the categories.

1623
02:32:26,974 --> 02:32:35,401
[SPEAKER_21]: I just wanted to make sure we said that again because we still have people contacting and saying, why are we paying X amount for an outside facility?

1624
02:32:35,482 --> 02:32:40,907
[SPEAKER_21]: But again, I know that you always eloquently put it to rest.

1625
02:32:41,007 --> 02:32:43,089
[SPEAKER_21]: So again, I would just ask you the process.

1626
02:32:43,628 --> 02:32:44,308
[SPEAKER_02]: Certainly, yes.

1627
02:32:44,748 --> 02:32:48,090
[SPEAKER_02]: So CPA funds can go towards three different categories.

1628
02:32:48,210 --> 02:32:50,150
[SPEAKER_02]: One of them is historic preservation.

1629
02:32:50,991 --> 02:32:54,632
[SPEAKER_02]: And the purpose of CPA is to always support community.

1630
02:32:55,152 --> 02:32:57,933
[SPEAKER_02]: That's first and foremost, our community gathering spaces.

1631
02:32:58,683 --> 02:33:03,426
[SPEAKER_02]: So yes, it is a church, but first and foremost, it is a community gathering space.

1632
02:33:03,826 --> 02:33:07,548
[SPEAKER_02]: They do food drives, they have community meetings there.

1633
02:33:08,068 --> 02:33:12,951
[SPEAKER_02]: And as I said, now they are hosting a childcare provider in their basement.

1634
02:33:12,991 --> 02:33:20,375
[SPEAKER_02]: So I understand people's concerns about this, but first and foremost, we're funding that it's a community supportive project.

1635
02:33:21,289 --> 02:33:25,231
[SPEAKER_02]: So, and I'm always happy to answer any questions if folks have questions on.

1636
02:33:25,731 --> 02:33:31,033
[SPEAKER_02]: What type of projects we fund, we just opened up our fiscal 27 CPA application round.

1637
02:33:31,093 --> 02:33:32,114
[SPEAKER_02]: So this is a great time.

1638
02:33:32,134 --> 02:33:33,414
[SPEAKER_02]: If folks have questions.

1639
02:33:33,434 --> 02:33:39,617
[SPEAKER_02]: Uh, Teresa DuPont, you know, I'm, I'm up in the, the planning department, always happy to talk to people about.

1640
02:33:40,217 --> 02:33:43,379
[SPEAKER_02]: Projects potential projects, past projects, whatever it may be.

1641
02:33:45,774 --> 02:33:46,414
[SPEAKER_21]: Thank you again.

1642
02:33:46,454 --> 02:34:01,440
[SPEAKER_21]: I know that this is redundant, but I think it's important that people understand the impact that the CPA makes on our, especially our historical community and making sure that we feel everybody, everybody feels welcome in this process.

1643
02:34:01,460 --> 02:34:02,020
[SPEAKER_21]: So thank you.

1644
02:34:02,520 --> 02:34:02,920
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you.

1645
02:34:04,301 --> 02:34:04,701
[SPEAKER_08]: Thank you.

1646
02:34:08,262 --> 02:34:08,642
[SPEAKER_09]: Thank you.

1647
02:34:08,982 --> 02:34:13,484
[SPEAKER_09]: Um, thank you, um, Teresa for your hard work on,

1648
02:34:14,812 --> 02:34:20,876
[SPEAKER_09]: Well, really on everything CPA related, but especially with these two projects.

1649
02:34:21,877 --> 02:34:39,168
[SPEAKER_09]: These two are really treasured institutions of the city, the Royal House being a place where we reflect upon our history, the significance of Medford going back centuries, but also the harm and damage done to people who lived here then.

1650
02:34:40,956 --> 02:34:45,319
[SPEAKER_09]: The Shiloh Baptist Church is the center of community, as you have talked about.

1651
02:34:46,100 --> 02:34:47,701
[SPEAKER_09]: And so these are important projects to me.

1652
02:34:49,343 --> 02:35:04,534
[SPEAKER_09]: To kind of back up what Councilor Scarpelli was saying, agree with it or disagree with it, there is Supreme Court precedent on not excluding religious institutions that would otherwise qualify for funds like these.

1653
02:35:05,255 --> 02:35:06,796
[SPEAKER_09]: It would actually be illegal to do so.

1654
02:35:08,637 --> 02:35:29,594
[SPEAKER_09]: the, according to the Trinity Lutheran Church of Columbia versus Comer, that is a case where there was a similar kind of municipal grant structure and Missouri had denied a religious preschool access to the state grants for rubber playground resurfacing.

1655
02:35:31,275 --> 02:35:36,880
[SPEAKER_09]: And because the institution otherwise qualified this, aside from its religious character,

1656
02:35:37,815 --> 02:35:43,977
[SPEAKER_09]: The Supreme Court said at the time that that imposed a penalty on free exercise of religion.

1657
02:35:44,577 --> 02:35:55,140
[SPEAKER_09]: Again, residents can agree or disagree with that decision, but that is what the law says, and so we have to be careful in our decisions.

1658
02:35:55,240 --> 02:36:06,603
[SPEAKER_09]: And the CPC, the Community Preservation Committee is, in my opinion, following the word of the law and being careful with our decision-making process.

1659
02:36:14,052 --> 02:36:16,474
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you for your comments there.

1660
02:36:16,874 --> 02:36:28,022
[SPEAKER_02]: I will also just add to stress that as the CPC, the committee that reviews these applications, we funded plenty of church projects in the past, but we've always been adamant.

1661
02:36:29,358 --> 02:36:39,147
[SPEAKER_02]: a condition of the funding that no CPA funds, no tax public funds go towards anything that has religious imagery or iconography.

1662
02:36:39,968 --> 02:36:45,794
[SPEAKER_02]: Um, so just to kind of solidify that, you know, I just wanted to share that and make sure folks were understanding of that.

1663
02:36:47,956 --> 02:36:54,422
[SPEAKER_02]: Um, I'm happy to talk about Royal house, but you know, there's obviously I defer to the council if there's further questions on Shiloh.

1664
02:36:59,122 --> 02:37:02,183
[SPEAKER_02]: Okay, I'll be brief on Royal House.

1665
02:37:02,763 --> 02:37:11,345
[SPEAKER_02]: So they're seeking $38,000 to address some urgent repairs needed on the section of the historic brick perimeter wall that serves as the property's boundary.

1666
02:37:11,365 --> 02:37:21,068
[SPEAKER_02]: You know, this wall is approaching 150 years old and the original mortar is shockingly failing in this section and is bowing into the abutters backyard.

1667
02:37:22,067 --> 02:37:32,049
[SPEAKER_02]: The Royal House Association has always taken their role as both a steward of the museum and as a neighbor very seriously, so they jumped right on the issue when it was brought to their attention.

1668
02:37:32,990 --> 02:37:42,332
[SPEAKER_02]: So this funding would see the wall be repaired with new mortar, new flashing, and to help kind of like reseat the wall so that it does not, you know, it reduces its risk of collapse here.

1669
02:37:43,838 --> 02:37:49,723
[SPEAKER_02]: I'll also just do a quick plug that the Royal House, they are now open for the season for their house tours.

1670
02:37:50,124 --> 02:37:55,188
[SPEAKER_02]: I would encourage folks if they're in the neighborhood, it's open on Saturdays and Sundays from 1-4.

1671
02:37:55,248 --> 02:37:58,411
[SPEAKER_02]: Come on down, take a tour.

1672
02:37:58,611 --> 02:38:02,534
[SPEAKER_02]: We're very blessed to have such a rich piece of American and Medford history right in our backyard.

1673
02:38:03,795 --> 02:38:06,518
[SPEAKER_02]: I'm happy to take any questions on the Royal House project.

1674
02:38:07,338 --> 02:38:08,059
[SPEAKER_20]: Move to approve.

1675
02:38:13,923 --> 02:38:17,746
[SPEAKER_07]: This is what happens when you can unmute yourself.

1676
02:38:21,650 --> 02:38:23,712
[SPEAKER_07]: On the motion of Council, I'm going to approve.

1677
02:38:23,892 --> 02:38:25,694
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you, Teresa, for the presentation.

1678
02:38:26,294 --> 02:38:31,179
[SPEAKER_07]: Seconded by Councilor Callahan.

1679
02:38:33,260 --> 02:38:34,141
[SPEAKER_07]: Any further discussion?

1680
02:38:37,244 --> 02:38:38,505
[SPEAKER_07]: Seeing none, Mr. Clerk, please call the roll.

1681
02:38:39,526 --> 02:38:40,327
[SPEAKER_19]: Councilor Callahan.

1682
02:38:42,522 --> 02:38:43,222
[SPEAKER_19]: Councilor Lemming?

1683
02:38:43,943 --> 02:38:44,343
[SPEAKER_16]: Yes.

1684
02:38:46,044 --> 02:38:46,764
[SPEAKER_19]: Councilor Mullane?

1685
02:38:46,784 --> 02:38:46,844
[SPEAKER_19]: Yes.

1686
02:38:49,206 --> 02:38:50,086
[SPEAKER_19]: Councilor Scott Pelley?

1687
02:38:50,106 --> 02:38:50,186
[SPEAKER_19]: Yes.

1688
02:38:51,026 --> 02:38:51,767
[SPEAKER_19]: Councilor Singh?

1689
02:38:51,787 --> 02:38:53,168
[SPEAKER_17]: Yes.

1690
02:38:53,188 --> 02:38:53,968
[SPEAKER_19]: Vice President Lazaro?

1691
02:38:53,988 --> 02:38:54,128
[SPEAKER_19]: Yes.

1692
02:38:55,049 --> 02:38:55,649
[SPEAKER_19]: President Pierce?

1693
02:38:56,629 --> 02:38:56,910
[SPEAKER_07]: Yes.

1694
02:38:56,930 --> 02:38:59,351
[SPEAKER_07]: 7 in the affirmative, none in the negative, the motion passes.

1695
02:39:00,690 --> 02:39:01,631
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you.

1696
02:39:01,651 --> 02:39:01,631
26, 1, 2, 3.

1697
02:39:02,471 --> 02:39:04,473
[SPEAKER_07]: Submitted by Mayor Brando, Lungo Kern.

1698
02:39:04,533 --> 02:39:08,235
[SPEAKER_07]: Capital Stabilization Fund Appropriation Request, Curtis Tufts Capital Needs Assessment.

1699
02:39:08,255 --> 02:39:21,124
[SPEAKER_07]: Dear President, mayors and city councilors, I respectfully request and recommend that your honorable body approve an appropriation from the Capital Stabilization Fund in the amount of $17,500.00 to fund a capital needs assessment of the Curtis Tufts High School in support of planning for the building's future use.

1700
02:39:21,585 --> 02:39:23,186
[SPEAKER_07]: Capital Stabilization Fund has a balance of $5,569,841.96.

1701
02:39:23,226 --> 02:39:24,787
[SPEAKER_07]: Director of Facilities David McIntyre will be available

1702
02:39:29,170 --> 02:39:29,851
[SPEAKER_07]: Questions?

1703
02:39:29,911 --> 02:39:31,292
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you for your kind attention to this matter.

1704
02:39:31,352 --> 02:39:33,633
[SPEAKER_07]: Respectfully submitted, Brianna Leocurne, mayor.

1705
02:39:33,874 --> 02:39:34,354
[SPEAKER_07]: She's the mayor.

1706
02:39:34,914 --> 02:39:36,035
[SPEAKER_07]: All right, David, let's go.

1707
02:39:36,055 --> 02:39:36,756
[SPEAKER_10]: How we doing?

1708
02:39:37,396 --> 02:39:40,138
[SPEAKER_10]: I would just add that I support assessments like this.

1709
02:39:40,218 --> 02:39:53,308
[SPEAKER_10]: I think they give us a great perspective and level of groundwork for making future decisions, especially when it comes to our buildings as assets that are vital to the city and services that we can provide now and going forward.

1710
02:39:54,926 --> 02:39:57,628
[SPEAKER_10]: I will take any questions if anyone has any.

1711
02:39:57,648 --> 02:40:06,333
[SPEAKER_07]: One quick question, is the motivation for this essentially that the plan is to move the Curtis Tufts back integrated into the new Medford High School, so we will need to do something with this building?

1712
02:40:07,273 --> 02:40:21,141
[SPEAKER_10]: I don't know the full concept of what future plans for this building are, but I know that there's been a lot of city services and departments who, including what you just mentioned, who are looking at potentially using space in this building, so.

1713
02:40:21,782 --> 02:40:21,942
[SPEAKER_10]: Great.

1714
02:40:22,885 --> 02:40:23,025
[SPEAKER_07]: Great.

1715
02:40:23,185 --> 02:40:26,147
[SPEAKER_07]: I'll go to Vice President Lazaro and then Councilor Malauulu.

1716
02:40:27,568 --> 02:40:33,972
[SPEAKER_13]: I couldn't agree with you more that it's important to have an assessment of the assets for the city and I motion to approve.

1717
02:40:35,153 --> 02:40:37,094
[SPEAKER_07]: Councilor Malauulu.

1718
02:40:37,734 --> 02:40:39,215
[SPEAKER_03]: Thank you for bringing this.

1719
02:40:39,295 --> 02:40:40,756
[SPEAKER_03]: I just had a couple of quick questions.

1720
02:40:40,996 --> 02:40:43,778
[SPEAKER_03]: Who is actually going to be doing the capital needs assessment?

1721
02:40:45,499 --> 02:40:48,441
[SPEAKER_03]: Do you know what firm is going to be doing that or who's going to be running it?

1722
02:40:48,461 --> 02:40:49,381
[SPEAKER_03]: We're still deciding on that.

1723
02:40:49,461 --> 02:40:50,082
[SPEAKER_03]: You're still deciding.

1724
02:40:50,442 --> 02:40:50,922
[SPEAKER_03]: Do you know like

1725
02:40:52,723 --> 02:40:54,624
[SPEAKER_03]: How are you going to come to that decision?

1726
02:40:54,704 --> 02:40:56,945
[SPEAKER_03]: Are you putting out bids or what does that look like right now?

1727
02:40:58,026 --> 02:41:00,187
[SPEAKER_10]: I believe that we're still waiting.

1728
02:41:00,707 --> 02:41:09,312
[SPEAKER_10]: We reached out to a couple different groups to see final numbers, but I believe that it's such a number that doesn't have to go out for a formal bid.

1729
02:41:09,472 --> 02:41:14,175
[SPEAKER_10]: I believe it could be fulfilled with just three quotes.

1730
02:41:15,115 --> 02:41:15,376
[SPEAKER_03]: Okay.

1731
02:41:15,436 --> 02:41:17,757
[SPEAKER_10]: I would double check with the procurement department on that.

1732
02:41:18,410 --> 02:41:18,710
[SPEAKER_03]: Okay.

1733
02:41:19,311 --> 02:41:22,433
[SPEAKER_03]: And I guess who's going to be providing?

1734
02:41:22,513 --> 02:41:29,960
[SPEAKER_03]: Is it you working directly with them, the vendor, with the requirements and timeline and all the needs that they have around that facility, around the building?

1735
02:41:30,000 --> 02:41:31,000
[SPEAKER_10]: I would be working with them.

1736
02:41:31,961 --> 02:41:37,286
[SPEAKER_10]: I would be in contact with Ken Lord as well, who has some of the information that would be used for this.

1737
02:41:37,306 --> 02:41:45,773
[SPEAKER_10]: You know, typically they look at any kind of documentation that exists and any kind of staffing that may have interacted with kind of maintenance schedules.

1738
02:41:47,097 --> 02:41:52,260
[SPEAKER_10]: I would primarily be working on this, but it would be in conjunction with some of his support.

1739
02:41:52,760 --> 02:41:53,000
[SPEAKER_03]: Okay.

1740
02:41:53,301 --> 02:41:53,641
[SPEAKER_03]: Thank you.

1741
02:41:55,222 --> 02:41:56,022
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you, Councilor Mulane.

1742
02:41:56,222 --> 02:41:57,223
[SPEAKER_07]: Any further questions?

1743
